Many people wish to be able to search for issues that have been in some state _in the past_.  For example, all issues that have once been Reopened.

calendar-system.css refers to invalid image. menuarrow.gif doesn't exist in the style folder location. We'll need to fix this and see what the effect on the GUI is.


.calendar .nav {
  background: ButtonFace url(menuarrow.gif) no-repeat 100% 100%;
}

Im working on a plugin which stores the executer of a transition into a customfield. Plugin lets you choose the customfield for storing. When I use a normal textfield or userpickerfield everything works fine. If i take a readonly customfield for storing it just works the first time -> field is updated. But theres no way updating it  a second time -> field keeps always the same value. Is this a bug or feature?


if (cfType.equals("com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:userpicker"))
{
   cf.updateValue(issue,executer);
   issue.store();
}

else

{
  cf.updateValue(issue,executer.getName());
  issue.store();	
}

